items.title: Czechs appeal for EU help with Radio Free Europe after Trump cuts
items.description: The US president signed an executive order on Friday to stop funding the American global broadcaster, following criticism from Elon Musk.

items.title: What to expect from Trump's phone call with Putin on Ukraine
items.description: The US president says elements of a Ukraine ceasefire have been agreed, but "much remains" to be worked on.

items.title: Israel launches waves of strikes on Gaza with more than 400 reportedly killed
items.description: The Israeli military says it is targeting Hamas "terror targets", but eyewitnesses describe a nightmare scenario.

items.title: At least 12 dead in Honduras plane crash
items.description: Officials who took part in the emergency operations said that five people were rescued.

items.title: Chinese state media hails Trump's cuts to Voice of America
items.description: State newspaper gloated that the network has "now been discarded by its own government like a dirty rag".
